President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Judge Amy Coney Barrett of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit to fill the Supreme Court vacancy left by the late Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg. Judge Barrett has been a judge on the Seventh Circuit since 2017 and has a background in constitutional and statutory interpretation. She has also held positions at Notre Dame Law School, the University of Virginia Law School, and George Washington University Law School. Additionally, she has clerked for Justice Antonin Scalia and Judge Laurence H. Silberman. Judge Barrett graduated with honors from Rhodes College and Notre Dame Law School, where she ranked first in her class.